<br>
Actually that shows that you haven't been playing as long as some others. Before swarm kiting was around, charm WAS used as a CC tool, all the time. It could be used to solo as well, charm kiting. Stick your charmed mob on 1 other mob. People want the ability back to use charm as a CC tool. The whole reason we don't have that ability is because of swarm kiting. <br>
<br>
Someone asked a dev at one of the fanfairs to have our charm cap raised, he said he knows what bards do with charm, and in its current state that is not going to happen. So we get the gimped version, which is really only good for swarm kiting. If they don't like swarm kiting so much, why put in a charm where that is its only real use? Sounds like they dropped the ball a bit there.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And, having played a necro who is not too far from my bard, I get to see a slower and safer experience rate as well.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
This is the exact reason they don't want people swarm kiting. Necros are considered one of the more powerful soloers, yet you are saying you can get more exp swarming with a bard. They don't want one class to be able to get exp that much faster then all the rest, never mind faster then a group. Sure someone has to be on top as the fastest soloer, but it should not be faster then a group, they have stated this many times. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
